  ![Next.js logo next to upward trending SEO ranking graph showing number one position with green and blue gradient background](https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/1*ancdWcjhE15fLWPesBBUdw.png)
  
  **If your building web apps with react and watching your competitors all of sudden rank ahead of you on google, chances are you are missing Next. js’s SEO superpowers.** Most developers know Next. Js is super-fast but few know that it is the most superior SEO framework you can get today, albeit — in secret.
  
  For the past three years, I have been using **Next.js** to build production apps. and there are SEO results that have literally blown my mind since getting my hands on it. Now, I want to show you exactly how to use this framework to own the search results.
  
  ## Why Next.js Crushes Traditional React for SEO
  
  When it comes to SSR, Vanilla React apps render on the client side so what a search engine sees is an empty HTML shell until JavaScript execution happens. Next.js With server-side rendering (SSR) and static site generation (SSG) flips this on its head and provides crawlers with fully-formed HTML right away.
  
  As stated in Google’s documentation, page speed and Core Web Vitals are both ranking factors. Next. js comes with optimization for both out of the box — no…
  
  ## 5 REAL SEO Tactics That Actually Work
  
  ### 1\. Dynamic Metadata API (Next. js 13+)
  
  With the new Metadata API, SEO setup is now hilariously clean:
  
  ```
  import { Metadata } from 'next';
  
  export const metadata: Metadata = {
    title: 'Best TypeScript Patterns for 2025',
    description: 'Learn advanced TypeScript patterns that scale with your team',
    openGraph: {
      title: 'Best TypeScript Patterns for 2025',
      description: 'Learn advanced TypeScript patterns that scale',
      images: ['/og-image.jpg'],
    },
  };
  
  export default function BlogPost() {
    return <article>Your content here</article>;
  }
  ```
  
  Way better than React Helmet — type safe, server rendered, 0 client cost.
  
